Hello everyone,
Here's the deal, I'm making this post because since July 1st I've had a bad trip on LSD,
I need to say that before this bad trip I was hitting 20 pills a day and I was doing some 1 week every two months with some heavy shit (Taz, coke, LSD, and everything else)...For 3 years,
now i'm gonna tell you how it went down.
Have a good week, waiting for you
Friday night everyone is doing well
We consumed 5 grams of speed plus all the MD.
Saturday morning after a sleepless night I'm going to work just the morning from 9am to 12pm in the afternoon,
We didn't continue.
I kept on my side tapping cartridges and tapping speed,
a coworker is holding the glass with a drop of the LSD vial
I hesitated at first then after I told myself come on I'll take it (something I shouldn't have done).
The evening continues normally and the two other so-called colleagues had decided to make us drink super good colleagues....
On this famous beach there were a lot of people and one of the two colleagues told us there's someone looking for trouble, we're gonna fight...
I'm thinking the product needs to go down because I wouldn't be able to fight like that
so I forced myself to resist the product
The paranoia is starting to engulf me, everyone's making a scene
The two other colleagues who hadn't taken anything, started looking for the guys who are mad at us
I being totally freaking out, I thought it was going to go away at any moment.
Time passes, nothing happens.
So we're leaving the beach and then we're going to my place,
I ask them if the guys are following us.
He doesn't respond.
We get to my place and he leaves me hanging all alone at my place with my girlfriend who was sleeping...
I keep having bad dreams all night
Impossible to sleep, I'm thinking and at the slightest noise I come out with a bat....
The day is rising and I'm starting to fall asleep because I just realized there was nothing
The night passes normally,
I wake up and I'm still under the influence of LSD and the rest
I told myself it's normal
So we were on Sunday and the next day I had to work.
The day is passing normally
I'm gonna shoot up some dope then I'm gonna take a nap.
Sunday passes and Monday arrives
I still feel like crap.
I still think it's normal with the box I got....
So at 2 pm I was supposed to take the job
Right now I'm eating a little and I'm taking a big line of speed to have energy at work...
so I take the car and I'm going to work
Arrive at work, as soon as I open the store I start to get dizzy, my heart starts beating at 200 and I feel like I'm going to faint.
By reassuring me I'm going to buy some Snickers bars and something to drink,
After that I go back to work and another crisis...
Panicked I called my mom.. because the colleagues weren't there....
after that my mom took me to the doctor
He asks me what I did and I spill all the beans.
and my mom took it pretty well finally she knows I was shady..
The Doctor told me to wait for the product to go down, it will take a few months then that's it
I told him I had vision problems
I told him I had vision problems
he told me it was normal too and that it was going to go down
For my anxiety attacks he prescribed me lizanxia an anti-anxiety medication finally against anxiety
I take 1 in the morning 1 in the evening,
It calms me but the voices in my head won't stop,
It often gives me a good headache...
Following this bad experience, I stopped everything, no more bullets, nothing.
My girlfriend doesn't understand what's happening to me and she kinda doesn't care
I fired him.
My colleagues also don't care either so I fired him too.
At the same time I moved.
I currently live with my mom, but I found an apartment
but I can't live there because I have anxiety attacks.
Besides that, I have tons of thoughts in my head
It's been 5 months today since I did this bad and at the level of my sight I still look behind a mirror
Finally these troubles especially when it's sunny...
The voices in my head don't stop from morning till night...
My thoughts are getting confused from always doing the same thing
I feel like I'm living the same day every day.
I always have my work, I no longer have any friends except 2 cousins and my brother who are far from me.
I work alone too
and so all day I'm all alone except in the evening when there's my mom...
I'm going to see an ophthalmologist at the beginning of January but I don't think it's going to fix much.
In fact, I don't really know what to do anymore except wait and maybe get out of this...
Thank you for reading my message and sorry for the spelling mistakes.
If someone has already lived through this experience, can or could they give me some advice. Thank you
Hello to you Claude271. To start, I don't take LSD.
I think you should just see another doctor or a toxicologist (I don't know if that's the exact term)
If after 5 months you're still experiencing this kind of "side effect" it's really bad.
So without wanting to panic you, you should go see a toxicologist who I think will prescribe you a treatment or emergency cache.
Otherwise there are green numbers or specialized forums. Good luck. Peace
Hi Claude271,
For having gone through that state you describe many times (following mixtures of chatter, microdots, TAZ, ketamine, finally everything that passed through there),
If I can give you one piece of advice, it's simply to tell you that it's all psychological.
Basically, the more you stress about these things, the worse they'll get.
A really simple thing to do in these situations, you take deep breaths, you breathe slowly, and you settle into a place where you feel safe, and not too close to the walls (yeah sometimes you can feel like they're closing in on you).
After several months following a binge, especially when you mix substances, you can experience effects, especially after a sudden stop of the substances.
Don't worry, it's just a matter of time.
But as Claude532 said, seeing a psychiatrist can also help you get rid of those voices that are clogging up your head.
Keep up the good work, and stay positive.
Thank you to both of you for your answers
I'm gonna try to be patient,
